cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SOC

This paper discusses the use of altmetrics to measure the societal impact of research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as altmetrics are web-based metrics for scholarly material. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are also likely as the paper discusses the use of social media platforms to gather data for altmetrics and the broader impact of research on society. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of bibliometrics and peer review to measure research impact. Finally, cs.SOC (Social Computing) is also relevant as the paper discusses the social aspects of research impact.
